        {
            "title": "Solana-based True platform aims to provide smarter, transparent execution in decentralized markets through AI; targets U.S. market.",
            "id": "614de3f1-ab3d-49d9-93be-9d830e1142ba",
            "description": "Benjamin Bilski, representing the Solana-based AI trading platform True, mentioned that the accessibility of perpetual futures in the U.S. could validate their model and grow the market. The comment highlights the potential impact of regulatory clarity on decentralized derivatives and AI-driven trading. Bilski stated that although they do not actively target the U.S. market, global regulatory clarity is welcomed. He emphasized that if perpetuals are approved in the U.S., the model would be validated and market size expanded. He also noted that innovation in decentralized finance will persist with users still seeking transparency, instant access, and self-custody. True is set to launch its $TRUE token sale to support the first AI-native perpetuals DEX on Solana, aiming to combine high-speed off-chain execution.",
            "link": "https://www.markets.news/headlines/614de3f1-ab3d-49d9-93be-9d830e1142ba",
            "pub_date": "2025-09-06 05:21:19",
            "source": "unusualwhales",
            "kind": 1,
            "language": "en"
